1 "§ 113A-113. Areas of environmental concern; in general.
2 …
3 (b) The Commission may designate as areas of environmental concern any one or more
4 of the following, singly or in combination:
5 …
6 (2) Estuarine waters, that is, all the water of the Atlantic Ocean within the
7 boundary of North Carolina and all the waters of the bays, sounds, rivers, and
8 tributaries tributaries, excluding man-made ditches under G.S. 113A-103(8a),
9 thereto seaward of the dividing line between coastal fishing waters and inland
10 fishing waters, as set forth in the most recent official published agreement
11 adopted by the Wildlife Resources Commission and the Department of
12 Environmental Quality;
13 …
14 (5) Areas such as waterways and lands under or flowed by tidal waters or
15 navigable waters, excluding man-made ditches under G.S. 113A-103(8a), to
16 which the public may have rights of access or public trust rights, and areas
17 which the State of North Carolina may be authorized to preserve, conserve, or
18 protect under Article XIV, Sec. 5 of the North Carolina Constitution;
19 …
20 (b1) The Commission may not designate man-made ditches, as defined under
21 G.S. 113A-103(8a), as areas of environmental concern.
22 …."
23 SECTION 3.(c) G.S. 113-229(n)(3) reads as rewritten:
24 "(3) "Marshland" means any salt marsh or other marsh subject to regular or
25 occasional flooding by tides, including wind tides (whether or not the
26 tidewaters reach the marshland areas through natural or artificial
27 watercourses), provided this shall not include hurricane or tropical storm tides.
28 Salt marshland or other marsh shall be those areas upon which grow some,
29 but not necessarily all, of the following salt marsh and marsh plant species:
30 Smooth or salt water Cordgrass (Spartina alterniflora), Black Needlerush
31 (Juncus roemerianus), Glasswort (Salicornia spp.), Salt Grass (Distichlis
32 spicata), Sea Lavender (Limonium spp.), Bulrush (Scirpus spp.), Saw Grass
33 (Cladium jamaicense), Cattail (Typha spp.), Salt-Meadow Grass(Spartina
34 patens), and Salt Reed-Grass (Spartina cynosuroides). A marshland shall not
35 include any area contained within a man-made ditch, as defined under
36 G.S. 113A-103(8a)."
37 SECTION 4. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
38 law.
